    {
      "id": "sybil_6_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_6",
      "description": "Offering a mechanically sound FD3S chassis featuring the iconic 13B-REW rotary engine. This unit maintains excellent compression across both rotors, with the sequential twin-turbocharger system transitioning seamlessly at 4,500 RPM. The vacuum line 'rat's nest' has been simplified with high-temp silicone, and the cooling system is upgraded with an aluminum dual-pass radiator to mitigate heat soak. Power is delivered through a crisp five-speed manual transmission to a Torsen limited-slip differential. The double-wishbone suspension remains tight, providing the neutral handling and high-speed stability these cars are known for. Minor cosmetic wear consistent with age, but the longitudinal rigidity and powertrain performance are uncompromising. A turn-key example for the purist looking for a balanced power-to-weight ratio.",
